\begin_layout Standard
Figure 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "fig:Thread-creation-diagram"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset

 illustrates the creation of parallel processes and the information propagation mechanism in the parallel BGWO framework.
 Each thread 
\begin_inset Formula $1,2,…,N$
\end_inset

 corresponds to an independent processing unit (PU),
 which manages a subpopulation.
 The subpopulations evolve simultaneously,
 exploring different regions of the search space through the basic mechanisms of BGWO.
 Parallel execution allows for independent search for solutions,
 while at the same time supporting cooperation through propagation mechanisms.
 During this phase,
 selected high-quality solutions are transferred between subpopulations according to predefined exchange strategies.
 When a subpopulation finds a particularly good solution,
 its propagation to other subpopulations can accelerate the overall convergence.
 Overall,
 the combination of parallel exploration and controlled information exchange makes parallel BGWO more efficient,
 allowing a better balance between exploration and exploitation.
\end_layout

