\begin_layout Subsection*
4.8 Practical problems
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
To further examine the practical efficiency and scalability of the proposed optimization algorithm,
 two real-world engineering design problems were investigated:
 the GasCycle 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "GasCycle"
literal "false"

\end_inset

 and the Tandem Queueing System 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "Tandem"
literal "false"

\end_inset

.
 These problems were selected because they differ significantly in mathematical formulation and computational complexity,
 providing a comprehensive framework for evaluating the algorithm’s performance under diverse and realistic conditions.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Each problem was tested across multiple dimensional configurations,
 ranging from 25 to 500 variables,
 in order to assess how the algorithm behaves as the search space becomes more complex.
 For every configuration,
 the execution time in seconds was recorded as the main performance indicator.
 This experimental setup enables a direct comparison of how computational efficiency changes with increasing dimensionality.
\end_layout

